      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE HOOFANANNY NZ (11) ran fourth last start at Redcliffe over 1780m, beaten 10 metres. Not drawn to best so may need a 10/10 drive. This looks a sterner test than last time but she is good enough to take this out. BELMER BETTY (12) scored at this track two runs ago before having her colours lowered when second at her latest appearance over 1660m at this track, beaten 5.5 metres. May just need a bit of luck at some point from this difficult draw. Good enough to win a race of this calibre. TAYLORS FOUR (5) is a big chance following a run of three top-three finishes, the latest at Marburg four days ago. Real threat to the top selections. JIMMY BLING (1) is next best and gets every chance from a favourable draw.",
